cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.EDU 

The paper presents a novel technique for automatic program correction in MOOCs using a seq2seq neural network model, which is commonly used in natural language processing tasks such as machine translation. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper addresses issues related to software engineering and education, which could lead to categorization under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.EDU (Education). Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms to correct programs, which could also lead to categorization under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
